41 Wilcox and Cooper JJ returned to this subject at 574, saying: 
 As we have already observed, picketing which does not involve obstruction and besetting does not fall within the definition of 'industrial action'; it does not relate to the performance of work in the circumstances specified in para (a), (b), (c) or (d) of the definition.
